3.1 Instruction

Given a non-negative integer, 3 for example, return a string with a murmur: "1 sheepâ€¦2 sheepâ€¦3 sheepâ€¦". Input will always be valid, i.e.Â no negative integers.


3.2 YouTube Video


3.3 Solution Code
Solusi bar-bar

countSheep &lt;- function(num){
  if(num == 0){
    return("")
  } else {
    result &lt;- ""
    for(i in 1:num){
      result &lt;- paste(result, i, " sheep...", sep = "")
    }
    return(result)
  }
}

Solusi simple

countSheep &lt;- function(num){
  ifelse(num == 0, "", paste(1:num, "sheep...", collapse = ""))
}


3.4 Test

library(testthat)

test_that("Fixed tests", {
  expect_equal(countSheep(0), "")
  expect_equal(countSheep(1), "1 sheep...")
  expect_equal(countSheep(2), "1 sheep...2 sheep...")
  expect_equal(countSheep(3), "1 sheep...2 sheep...3 sheep...")
})

